verbose_text: In support of an acetate recapturing function of ACSS2, we noticed that cells that avidly consumed U- 13 C-acetate released relatively little 12 C-acetate (XREF_SUPPLEMENTARY A), arguing that ACSS2 captures exogenous acetate but also prevents the release of endogenously produced acetate by recapturing it.
evidence: ACSS2 captures exogenous acetate but also prevents the release of endogenously produced acetate
